57.0	Neal_Adams	Neal Adams	Neal Adams (born June 15, 1941) is an American comic book and commercial artist known for helping to create some of the definitive modern imagery of the DC Comics characters Superman, Batman, and Green Arrow; as the co-founder of the graphic design studio Continuity Associates; and as a creators-rights advocate who helped secure a pension and recognition for Superman creators Jerry Siegel and Joe Shuster.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/8/8e/NealAdams11.15.08ByLuigiNovi1.jpg/230px-NealAdams11.15.08ByLuigiNovi1.jpg
